Grammar of the valsim language
Its grammar is influenced by C's grammar
It shall be a LR grammar as most of the today's languages

## Token description

letter :
    | a
    | ..
    | z

digit :
    | 0
    | 1
    | ..
    | 9

id : letter (letter|digit)*


## Valsim Expression rules




## Valsim Declaration rules

declaration-list : 
    | declaration
    | declaration-list declaration 

declaration : 
    | function-declaration
    | var-declaration

function-declaration :
    | fct ( var-declaration ) : type statement

var-declaration : 
    | type id

type :
    | int
    | char
    | string

## Valsim Statement rules

statement : 
    | selection-statement
    | iteration-statement
    | statement-list
    | jump-statement

selection-statement :
    | if ( expression ) statement
    | if ( expression ) statement else statement
    | switch ( expression ) statement

iteration-statement : 
    | for ( expression ; expression ; expression ) statement
    | while ( expression ) statement
    | do statement while ( expression )

statement-list :
    | statement
    | statement-list statement

break-statement : 
    | break ;
   
return-statement : 
    | return statement;
    | return ;   
